Rune: Um...Clark and Maria...?
Sophie: Yea. I hope they come up with some clues...
Rune: Is that...Sanchez?
Sophie: Sanchez, why are you here?
Sanchez: I'm off work. I'm here to help look for Elio! He's basically the reason Rune and I are still alive~
Sophie: Really! I didn't know Sanchez was such a good guy!
Sanchez: Hey...HEY! I've always been a good guy!
Sophie: Just joking. Thanks, Sanchez!
Rune: Sanchez...let's go.
Sophie: Clark, Maria. Did you find any clues?
Clark: Nope. We searched all around here and found nothing.
Maria: Clark, look! A roasted chicken is flying!
Clark: That's a bird from the Shrine, Maria. What about you guys?
Sophie: Nothing...
Clark: These locations have nothing in common...
Maria: Air attack! Air attack! Air attack! Master and fellow comrades, scatter!
Clark: *sigh*...here we go again...
Maria: Roasted Chicken! Come play with Chu Chu and I!
Maria: Master Clark, you too!
Clark: ...Not now. My head hurts.
Sophie: Um...we don't need to save the bird...?
Sophie: *cough*...I mean, it seems like Maria really wants to play with you. Do you need to...
Clark: *sigh*...
Clark: Don't worry about it. Let's talk about the issue at hand. Could we have missed something on Elio's map?
Sophie: Um...
Sanchez: I-I-I think that maybe~ Elio just wanted to leave!
Sanchez: After all, he isn't from the Desert Kingdom, right?
Sophie: Really? But Clark said Elio wouldn't just...I...was it something I did...?
Maria: Clark, this roasted chicken is broken. It won't fly.
Clark: That's because you grabbed it and won't let it fly.
Clark: AHA!!!!!
Sophie: What's wrong!?
Clark: I just remembered, Elio is part of the Feather Clan!
Clark: Maria!
Maria: Yes, sir! Lift off in 3...2...
Rune: Lift...off?
Sanchez: How can she fly? Is she a monster?
Random Man: A beast! Help!
Random Woman: She wants to attack us! Run!!
Soldier Captain: Are those the flying monsters we've heard about on the news?
Clark: Hey! She's not a monster!
Soldier Captain: Ready! Scan!
Sophie: No!
Soldier Captain: This monster is too strong! Head back and call for reinforcements!
Clark: Maria, what did you see!?
Maria: Preparing for projection. Master, please wait a moment.
Sophie: Aren't these the locations that Elio marked off himself?
Clark: That's right...
Sophie: Eh? If you put these roads together...what pattern does this make?
Clark: I've never seen this before. But it looks human. If I had to guess, I'd say it was a Rune.
Sanchez: Wait a sec! Wait just one second! Are you saying that if you look at the new section of the city from the sky...
Clark: Then you'll see this mysterious Rune.
Clark: Down here it's impossible to see. Elio must have seen this from above.
Sophie: S-S-So Elio disappeared because——
